This Child Safety Report was sent to Oklahoma Human Services on 11/24/2024. Please contact John Adams (reporter) for additional information about the details contained herein.
View Original Report

Report Summary:
[ONLINE NOTICE]: This online report was received at the hotline on 11/24/2024 at 3:40 PM. [HOUSEHOLD]: Megan (mother), Jessica (age 9), and Austin (age 8). Megan's boyfriend Jeff may live in the home. The name of the children's biological father was not provided.
[MALTREATMENT]: The Reporter was told this information and observed the concerns. On 11/23/2024, Jessica (age 9) disclosed that she recently saw her mother, Megan, smoking something from a pipe. According to the Reporter, this was the first time Jessica witnessed her mother using the pipe, and Jessica did not know what the substance was. Jessica also disclosed that she saw her mother snort a white substance. Following the substance use, Jessica stated that Megan became very angry and locked her brother, Austin (age 8), in a closet. Jessica did not know how long Austin remained in the closet but described it as a very long time. Jessica further stated that Austin urinated in the closet and was not allowed to shower afterward. According to the Reporter, Jessica said that Austin is made to go into the closet a lot.
[ADULT/CHILD FUNCTIONING]: According the Reporter, [UNIQUE NEEDS]: Austin has a developmental delay and is nonverbal. He has also been diagnosed with ADHD and Autism. No unique needs or disabilities reported for Jessica [SUBSTANCE USE]: According to Jessica, Megan was seen smoking a substance from a pipe and snorting a white powder. Jessica stated this was the first time she witnessed her mother using these substances. After using, Megan reportedly became angry [DOMESTIC VIOLENCE]: No reports of domestic violence. [WORKER DANGERS]: There are dogs in the home. It is unclear whether they are aggressive, but Jessica mentioned the dogs frequently fight with each other. [LANGUAGE]: English. [NATIVE HERITAGE]: None reported.
[DISCIPLINE]: Megan uses a belt to hit the children. Sometimes she uses the metal part to hit the children too. She will also scream and cuss them out.
[PROTECTIVE CAPACITIES]: No reports of the parents or guardian doing anything to address the safety concerns.

NORA is an application that helps individuals make high-quality reports of child abuse or neglect. The completed reports are transmitted directly to state agencies for their review. Therefore, NORA is unable to provide any additional information beyond what is submitted through the software. If you require further details, please contact the Reporter or the contacts provided herein.
